user.name: Emilio Jesús Gallego Arias
user.bio: “La perfection est atteinte, non pas lorsqu'il n'y a plus rien à ajouter, mais lorsqu'il n'y a plus rien à retirer.”

commit.title: [ci] [gitlab] Add `interruptible: true` to jobs.
commit.message:
[ci] [gitlab] Add `interruptible: true` to jobs.

When a newer pipeline contains the same job, the job can be
interrupted, see:

https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/ci/yaml/README.html#interruptible

This should help with job limits (c.f. #11320 )

The patch is a bit unsatisfactory due to the duplication needed;
we could define a base job and use extends, but not sure it is worth
it for now.

https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/ci/yaml/README.html#interruptible

This should help with job limits (c.f. #11320 )

The patch is a bit unsatisfactory due to the duplication needed;
we could define a base job and use extends, but not sure it is worth
it for now.
